cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the application of bibliometric mapping techniques in the area of funded research networks, which involves topics related to digital libraries (cs.DL), social networks (cs.SI), scientific data management (cs.SD), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The focus on internet science also suggests a potential fit with the cs.CR sub-category, but this is less likely given the emphasis on bibliometric mapping techniques rather than security-specific research.
